' @id(USE-MAP-MOCKUPS)
' @desc(USE-MAP-MOCKUPS, "The /mdd-map skill (.claude/skills/mdd-map/SKILL.md, step 3a) now authors mockups: when run at whole-repository scope it auto-includes a current-side Salt mockup under .mdd/models/current/mockups/<name>.puml for every UI app it finds (today the repo-root mockups/ React app), with an MCK- id, a @ref to the use case it serves, and one @ui-element UIC id per data-testid so the contract mirrors the rendered UI. At feature/module scope mockups stay opt-in like the other non-use-case kinds. This makes a whole-repo map complete across all diagram kinds. Realized by SEQ-MAP-MOCKUPS; owned by CMP-MAP-SKILL.")
' Current use case (cycle 0020): the map skill's workflow now has a
' mockup step (3a); whole-repo scope emits mockups automatically.
title MDD map — auto-include mockups for whole-repo scope (current)

left to right direction

actor "Developer / Agent" as Dev <<added>>

rectangle "/mdd-map skill" {
  usecase "Map the whole repository\n(all diagram kinds)" as MapWhole
  usecase "Auto-include mockups\nfor any UI app found" as MapMockups
}

Dev --> MapWhole
MapWhole ..> MapMockups : <<include>>

note bottom of MapMockups
  Current (USE-MAP-MOCKUPS): whole-repo scope emits current-side
  MCK- Salt mockups for discovered UI apps (e.g. mockups/), with
  UIC ids mirroring data-testids. Feature/module scope keeps
  mockups opt-in.
end note
